Citation.sAbstract: Static dielectric constants of the binary mixtures of amides (formamide (FA), Nmethylformamide  (NMF), N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF), and N,N-dimethylacetamide  (DMA)) with alcohols (ethyl alcohol (EA) and ethylene glycol (EG)) over the entire  composition range have been investigated at 30 oC. The concentration dependent excess  dielectric constant of the binary mixtures reveal that the strength of H {bond molecular  interactions of amide family molecules vary significantly with EA and EG molecules and  these interactions are governed by their H!Vbonded self-association strength. The EA  molecules form the strong H!Vbonded 1:1 complexes with FA and NMF, whereas EG  molecules have the strong interactions only with NMF molecules and form stable adduct  of molar ratio 2:1 of NMF to EG molecules. The DMF and DMA have comparative weak  H!Vbonded interactions with both the EA and EG molecules, which is influenced by  molecular size of these amides.
Citation.sTitle: Dielectric constants and hydrogen bonded structures in amide-alcohol mixed solvents
